did.head: Descriptive Summary
did.abstract: Writings, correspondence, reports, studies, memoranda, legal and government documents, diaries, newspapers, photographs, and sound recording, relating to the history, politics, and government of Serbia and Yugoslavia, relations between Croatia and Serbia, activities of the Hrvatski Domobran in the United States, the communist party of Yugoslavia, the trial of Draza Mihailovic, and Serbian émigré affairs.

bioghist.head: Biography
bioghist.p: American political scientist; senior propaganda analyst, United States Department of Justice, 1942-1944; research analyst, United States Office of Strategic Services, 1944-1945; cultural attaché and public affairs officer, United States Embassy in Yugoslavia, 1947-1950.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content of Collection
scopecontent.p: Writings, correspondence, reports, studies, memoranda, legal and government documents, diaries, newspapers, photographs, and sound recording, relating to the history, politics, and government of Serbia and Yugoslavia, relations between Croatia and Serbia, activities of the Hrvatski Domobran in the United States, the communist party of Yugoslavia, the trial of Draza Mihailovic, and Serbian émigré affairs.
Correspondence, reports, clippings, and printed matter relating to A. Dragnich's career. Arranged alphabetically by subject.
Letters, reports, memoranda, printed material, and miscellany. Arranged alphabetically.
